Job Description:
COMPANY OVERVIEW
SKL is a prominent private real estate developer in Vietnam, renowned for its diversified portfolio spanning apartments, offices, hospitality, and property management. SKL is committed to delivering distinctive beauty, innovation and design through a unique blend of art, heritage and modern lifestyle.

POSITION OVERVIEW
Corporate Branding Manager is in charge of managing and coordinating branding activities/campaigns of assigned corporate tasks, working closely with other divisions and suppliers/vendors to ensure all tasks are running well according to BOD's requirements.

JOB RESPONSIBILITIES
1. Budget & Funding:
Prepare and get approval on the overall branding budget of all campaigns & tasks;
Manage and track the overall branding budget of all campaigns.
2. Branding campaigns & execution from BOD
Brainstorm & overall execution branding campaigns with other teams for additional assigned tasks out of annual branding plan (online & offline) from BOD.
3. Brand Development:
Branding audit & adjustment suggestion related to brand development;
Propose & develop suitable brand strategy according to BOD's vision;
Manage overall brand development within approved budget.
4. Brand Communication:
Brand communication audit & adjustment suggestion related to brand communication;
Propose & develop suitable brand communication as per task/campaign/IMC for both public and internal purposes;
Manage and work with other teams of Branding & Marketing Division to produce the branding materials for assigned tasks/campaigns;
Event Strategy and execution brief for events, exhibitions and promotional activities to increase brand visibility;
5. Market research & Implementation of initiatives related to the brand
Research and update trend and news on the market & related brands; Propose & implement efficient & suitable ideas/concepts for branding
6. Suppliers/agencies management
Build up and manage the vendors/ consultants for Corporate Branding Department;
Research for partnering up/Co-branding opportunities with matching brands;
Plan and develop a marketing partner network to execute the objectives of the brand strategy.
7. Partnership MKT Development
Plan and develop a marketing partner network to execute the objectives of the brand strategy.
8. Bidding & procurement
Build up and tracking bidding and procurement plans for Corporate Branding Department;
Work closely with Bidding and Procurement Division to execute the plan and align with company's procedure and KPIs;
9. Team development
Recruit & train team member(s) with the essential skills for branding marketing

Job Requirements:
- Bachelor's degree in Marketing, Journalism, Business Administration or a related field.
- At least 5 years experience in Marketing, Journalism, Business Administration or a related field.
- Strong written and verbal communication skills in English and Vietnamese.
- Strong project management skills;
- Strong research and report skills;
- Strong budget & funding skills;
- Communication & presentation skills;
- Creative skills (writing, visuals, designs…) & sense for visual designs
- Ability to come up with solutions and risk management;
- Strong analytical skills and the ability to interpret info for solution orientation;
- Essential Knowledge in Real Estate, Luxury product

Job Description:
JOB OVERVIEW
We are seeking an Admissions Officer to execute a diverse range of admissions tasks and support the engagement with diverse families in our community. The position will report to the Admissions Manager, be an integral part of the School’s Admissions & Enrollment Team, and work closely with many other departments of the School.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
• Manage the application process, ensuring a seamless and positive experience for prospective families;
• Advise new and visiting families on various aspects of the School, admissions guidelines, tuition fees and conduct campus tours;
• Represent the School with a professional and engaging presence—projecting warmth, confidence, and approachability when welcoming visitors, guiding tours, and supporting events;
• Support outreach efforts by attending external community events to build relationships and expand engagement with prospective and current families;
• Provide a high quality customer service to stakeholders, community members, prospective parents and visitors to the School;
• Oversee the organization of entrance exams, scheduling interviews, including liaison with appropriate Heads of Departments regarding the preparation and reporting of entrance assessments as needed;
• Support the planning and execution of admissions events to engage and inform prospective families;
• Oversee the logistics support to all admissions activities; ensure all School public areas related to admissions are organized, clean, professional and welcoming;
• Ensure confidentiality, accuracy, timely processing and digitization of all admissions related information and materials into the School System, including but not limited to documentation, assessments, notes, interest tracking and statistics;
• Systematically maintain and update applicant databases, information portals and hard copy files as needed;
• Monitor and provide the Admissions Manager with insights on families and market, assist in developing reports on enrollment trends;
• Collaborate with other School departments, such as Communications and Division Officer to carry out tasks related to school events and promotions, family relationship development and communication facilitation.

N.B.: These key responsibilities are not intended to be all-inclusive. The Admissions Officer may be required to perform other related duties assigned by their manager to meet the ongoing needs of the organization.

Job Requirements:
JOB REQUIREMENTS
• Proficiency in written and spoken English;
• Bachelor's degree in a related field;
• At least 3 years of experience in a relevant role
• Have a strong passion for education;
• Excellent customer service, attention to detail, interpersonal and communications skills, with the ability to engage with individuals from diverse backgrounds;
• Flexible and agile working style suitable for a greenfield school operations;
• Strong drive for organizational improvements;
• Team oriented and spirited.

Commitment to Child Safety at Dwight School Hanoi
At Dwight School Hanoi, the safety and well-being of our students are paramount. All employees are expected to fully embrace and adhere to our Child Protection and Safeguarding Policy, ensuring a secure and supportive environment for every student.

